<abstract><t>DHCP Forcerenew allows for the reconfiguration of a single host by forcing the DHCP client into a Renew state on a trigger from the DHCP server.  In Forcerenew Key Authentication the server exchanges a key with the client on the initial DHCP ACK that is used for subsequent validation of a Forcerenew message.</t></abstract>

